ProtoResult:
. "For every prime $p$ and every positive integer $n$, there 
   exists a finite field $F$ with $p^n$ elements. Furthermore, 
   any field of order $p^n$ is isomorphic to the splitting 
   field of $x^{p^n} -x$ over ${\mathbb Z}_p$."
